Privacy Policy

Last updated: December 04, 2023


This Privacy Policy outlines our practices regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of Your information when using the Service, explaining Your privacy rights and legal protections.


We use Your Personal data to provide and enhance the Service. By using it, You agree to the collection and use of information as per this Privacy Policy.


Definitions


For this Privacy Policy:


– Account: Your unique account to access our Service.


– Affiliate: An entity controlling, controlled by, or under common control with a party, where “control” means ownership of 50% or more of shares.


– Company: Refers to Debugshala, C.S Naidu Arcade, 204, Greater Kailash Road, Opposite Grotto, Old Palasia, Indore, Madhya Pradesh 452001.


– Cookies: Small files on Your device by a website, containing Your browsing history details.


– Country: Madhya Pradesh, India


– Device: Any device accessing the Service, e.g., computer, cellphone, or digital tablet.


– Personal Data: Information relating to an identified or identifiable individual.


– Service: The Website.


– Service Provider: Natural or legal person processing data on behalf of the Company, e.g., third-party companies facilitating the Service.


– Usage Data: Data collected automatically, e.g., IP address, browser type, pages visited.


 

Collecting and Using Your Personal Data


 

Types of Data Collected


 

Personal Data


When using Our Service, We may ask for personally identifiable information such as:


 

– Email address


– Phone number


– Usage Data


 

Usage Data


Collected automatically, it includes information like Device’s IP address, browser type, pages visited, and time spent.


 

Tracking Technologies and Cookies


We use Cookies and similar tracking technologies to monitor and improve the Service. Cookies can be “Persistent” or “Session” Cookies.


 

Use of Your Personal Data


The Company may use Personal Data for:


 

– Providing and maintaining the Service.


– Managing Your Account.


– Performing a contract.


– Contacting You for updates or informative communications.


– Providing news, offers, and general information.


– Managing Your requests.


– Business transfers.


– Other purposes like data analysis and improving the Service.


 

Retention of Your Personal Data


We retain Your Personal Data as long as necessary for the purposes stated in this Privacy Policy, complying with legal obligations.


 

Transfer of Your Personal Data


Your information may be processed and transferred to computers outside Your jurisdiction, ensuring adequate controls and security.


 

Delete Your Personal Data


You have the right to delete or request assistance in deleting the Personal Data collected about You.


 

Disclosure of Your Personal Data


 

Business Transactions


In mergers, acquisitions, or asset sales, Personal Data may be transferred with prior notice.


 

Law enforcement


The Company may disclose Your Personal Data if required by law or valid requests by public authorities.


 

Other legal requirements


The Company may disclose Your Personal Data to comply with legal obligations, protect rights or property, prevent wrongdoing, ensure personal safety, or protect against legal liability.


 

Security of Your Personal Data


While We strive for security, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.


 

Children’s Privacy


Our Service does not address anyone under 13. If You are a parent and Your child provided Personal Data, contact Us for removal.


 

Links to Other Websites


We have no control over third-party sites. Review their Privacy Policies when visiting.


 

Changes to this Privacy Policy


We may update Our Privacy Policy, notifying You via email or a notice on the Service.


 

Contact Us


For questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us:


 

– Email: info@debugshala.com


– Phone: 8982385539
